        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer283418974" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9509754202247038332">Oh goodness, how do I rate thee? If I compare this book to more recent fare, it doesn&apos;t bode well, but if I think about it as a bastion of 80s romance goodness, it would rank pretty high. I had never read this infamous novel with the horseback sex scene and was convinced by a few good ladies in twitter to not only read it but to live tweet as I did. And so...I did. This is a fantastic book as long as you keep in mind when it was written. If published today I think it would suffer a great deal of</span>
  <span id="freeText9509754202247038332" style="display:none">Oh goodness, how do I rate thee? If I compare this book to more recent fare, it doesn't bode well, but if I think about it as a bastion of 80s romance goodness, it would rank pretty high. I had never read this infamous novel with the horseback sex scene and was convinced by a few good ladies in twitter to not only read it but to live tweet as I did. And so...I did. This is a fantastic book as long as you keep in mind when it was written. If published today I think it would suffer a great deal of eye rolling. He changes his name form White Thunder to Colt Thunder to blend in with the white men....uh, you know things like this. Because it's WHITE that makes everyone believe he is an Indian not Thunder for a last name? <br /><br />At any rate, I'm glad I read it, I had fun tweeting it. I never threw my iPad across the room, eye rolling abounds, a whole lot of WTFckry, but it was all in good spirit. <br /><br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="9509754202247038332" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


